  "texts": [
    "Interpretable ML approaches, such as deep forest algorithms and methods that incorporate prior knowledge like microbial interaction networks, are emerging to address this issue (Räz, 2024).",
    "The second barrier is the scarcity of large, high-quality, and correctly labeled microbiome datasets needed to train ML models effectively (Schloss, 2018).",
    "Additionally, ensuring data quality through techniques like deduplication, class balancing, outlier removal, and imputation is crucial.",
    "Lastly, selecting, evaluating, and tuning the right ML model for a specific task can be challenging, but a rich ecosystem of libraries and frameworks, as well as synthetic microbiome datasets, can aid in model development and benchmarking (Hernández Medina et al., 2022).",
    "The challenges faced by ML in terms of metadata can be analogously compared to the complexities encountered in taxonomic annotation of bacteria, as discussed in the previous article by Mathieu et al. (2022)."
  ],
